L201D ␴32 is promptly degraded in vivo, similar to wild-type ␴32. Wild-type ␴32 is stabilized in dnaK mutants (17, 18), and ␴32
mutants with a reduced afﬁnity for DnaK are stabilized in a wild-
type strain (8, 26). Based on these reports and the above results, the degradation of L201D ␴32, which has a reduced afﬁnity for
DnaK, should be suppressed in comparison to that of wild-type ␴32. To distinguish plasmid-encoded ␴32 from chromosome-encoded wild-type ␴32, plasmids encoding wild-type and mutant ␴32
with six histidine residues at the C terminus were transformed
into a wild-type strain of E. coli (MC4100). The level of L201D ␴32-His was similar to that of wild-type ␴32-His, whereas the level of I54A ␴32-His was lower than that of wild-type ␴32-His (Fig. 5A), because I54A ␴32-His was expressed from the weak trc promoter.
When the levels of major heat shock proteins (DnaK, GroEL, and DnaJ) that are upregulated by ␴32 were examined by immunoblotting, they were higher in cells producing I54A ␴32-His than in cells producing wild-type ␴32-His, as described previously (26), whereas those in cells producing L201D ␴32-His were the same as those in cells producing wild-type ␴32-His (Fig. 5A). Next, the stability of ␴32-His was assessed. After chloramphenicol was
added to the culture medium to inhibit protein synthesis, the level of L201D ␴32-His rapidly decreased at a rate that was similar to that of wild-type ␴32-His, whereas I54A ␴32-His degradation was
suppressed as described previously (Fig. 5B) (26). To examine the dependence of L201D ␴32-His degradation on
DnaK, we used a ⌬dnaK mutant strain (KY1459) in which the
dnaK gene was partially replaced with a chloramphenicol resis-
tance gene (cat) (34). The replacement of the dnaK gene results in
a barely detectable level of DnaJ expression from the downstream
gene in the dnaK-dnaJ operon due to a polar effect (35). Expres-
sion vectors carrying the rpoH genes with six histidine codons could not be transformed into the ⌬dnaK strain, potentially reﬂecting the toxic effect of stabilizing both ␴32 and ␴32-His, because high activity of ␴32 is deleterious to cell growth (e.g., the gene encoding I54A ␴32, which is a hyperactive ␴32, cannot be cloned
under control of the intact trc promoter). Therefore, these plas-
mids were cotransformed with an expression vector carrying the

